title.narrative: Indonesia Clean Energy Development - II (ICED II Project)

description.narrative: (Indonesia): With an annual growth rate of 7% to 10%, the Government of Indonesia (GOI) is struggling to meet current energy demand. In the electricity sub-sector alone, Indonesia requires an estimated additional 35 gigawatts (GW) of power generation capacity within the next 5yrs. The current installed capacity is 43.5 GW. The 2014 National Energy Policy outlines the GOI's priorities in enhancing energy security and diversity; it calls for a significant increase in the contribution of new and renewable energy sources from the current level of approximately 8% to 23% by 2025. ..To advance the Indo-Pacific Strategy, ICED II works with key stakeholders in the energy sector to accelerate Indonesia's energy sector transformation to achieve targets by: 1) building GOI's capacity to implement energy planning to achieve 100% electrification ratio by 2020, 2) promoting transparent and globally accepted procurement procedures to drive investment in the renewable energy sector, 3) enhancing the capacity of Indonesia's electricity company to plan, procure, and integrate renewable energy into the power grid, and 4) assisting the private sector, incl. project developers, banks, and other financial institutions, to realize priority projects. USAID helps create a level playing field for private sector investment in renewable energy market valued at approx. $12 billion. ICED II contributes to the U.S. Mission objective of supporting Indonesia's greater global and regional role promoting democratic values, rule of law, and protecting the environment, public health, and other shared priorities. ICED II will support GOI to be more capable in planning, financing and implementing solutions for development in addressing energy demands and accelerating Indonesia's energy sector transformation, and the Private Sector engagement to be more effectively in catalyzing sustained investment in renewable energy sector. This contributes to the IPS energy initiative...
